HEADWORD: Weils disease
<hw>Weil's disease</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An acute
infectious febrile disease, resembling typhoid fever, with muscular
pains, disturbance of the digestive organs, jaundice, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

